	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64378118"><p>First, we've seen foreign investment scams before like the foxconn deal.   Once washington doesn't care about this anymore, we'll be back to square one.  Second, we also need a packaging plant built in the US or there's no point in this plant.  If they have to ship chips outside of the country to be packaged, they are just wasting shipping time.   That should have been a requirement for grants. Finally, it would have made more sense to put the money into Intel from a national security perspective.  What if china invades taiwan in the future and we have no chip production?</p></div>
