		<div id="comment_body_64379084"><em>In this case there really is quite a good tie to national defense - both for ensuring supply, and guarding against trojan horses.</em>

<br> <br>

So why not for green energy?  Would seem stupid to rely on only one or two forms of energy to keep the country running. Why not spread it out to several different forms of energy production so there's no single point of failure (Texas excluded)?

<br> <br>

A steady supply of energy would definitely fall under national defense considering how much the military, and the country, relie</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64379084">

</div>
